cross: Aerangis leuteoalba v. rhodosticta x Aerangis hyaloides

measurements.description: Approxiamately four hundred twenty-five flowers and 25 buds on 25 left-sweeping up-to 26-cm inflorescences; incredibly well-grown, immaculate, very compact plant, 22 cm wide, 15 cm tall, 16-cm hardwood branch mount; flowers white; sepals and petals lanceolate; lip spatulate, spur 1.8 cm; column and anther cap bright yellow; substance medium; texture diamond dust.
